span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 1:42:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5184.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunarean Signet Ring.</span><hr size=1>   Not really, unless you can convince a group to go to Plane of Mischief which is pretty difficult nowdays as the zone is a barren wasteland.   No real incentive to fight to PoM or enter the zone with the horrible drop rates of cards (need cards to make PoM armor).  Also, they increased the difficulty of all the mobs - it used to be a caster xp spot where groups of casters could all join together and even druids could tank the mobs if slowed.  Now, they changed the mobs to encourage bringing melee along, but no melee ever go cause it is really hard to bind there and there is no melee armor except for monks. <p>Fayne Dethe<BR> Level 60 Druid of Xegony<BR>Havenlight</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 3:18:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5184.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/ligsmall.jpg width=100 height=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunarean Signet Ring.</span><hr size=1> I still wear mine. With the wis cap being raised I think its worth more now than it was before.<br><br>However, as stated, PoM is the issue. PoM has been buffed, drops have been nerfed, its a graveyard. Shame too as it was a nice idea. Location of the entrance coupled with all of the other issues just killed it.<br><br>Anyway, the rest maybe a little time consuming if you are actively pursuing it, but if you have the PoM piece the rest is quite simple. <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide Guildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br>"You must do the thing you think you cannot do." - Eleanor Roosevelt<br>"When life looks like Easy Street there is danger at your door." - Robert Hunter</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqueyla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queyla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 6:20:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5184.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.manastorm.org/images/queyla-sig.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunarean Signet Ring.</span><hr size=1> Aye, I wear my ring 95% of the time now.<br><br>Kind of a satisfying quest all things considered.<br><br>Just gotta see if you can get a group in PoM to smoke the horse for the drop and then port out.  That (imo) would be far and away the hardest part.<br><br>Queyla Beefcake<br>Havenlight Guild<br>Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphreaky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phreaky