sometime I would.. but I'm not even in a big rush to do that really since 65 mana on top of the hp seems like no big deal.<br><br>Like you I first saw that tunarean signet ring quest and went &quot;OOH OH MY GOD NEED, OOH@!!!&quot; Then later learned how hard it would be to even get to the plane of mischief and how my guild never goes there and kind of forgot it.<br><br>If I went to all the bother to get it I'd still wear the 6 ac 65 hp rings and maybe stick it on for a trak raid or whatever. Really you start to find that in most raid situations with okay resists and the stuff other classes have like bard resist songs, DMF, your own circles, etc, you are more or less fine. At that point it seems far better to pile on any HP and possibly AC stuff instead of resists. I'm only 55 but people in my guild who are 60 tell me its even more that way then, they res more because they are 60 than piling on resist gear. <p><center><BR><img src=http://www.thisismycool.com/aandaie/imagesP/55aan_s.jpg height=186 width=480><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79246>Aandaie 55 Druid's Magelo</a><BR><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82044>Aaelandri 38 Cleric's Magelo</a><BR></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usiulzeuqzav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siul Zeuqzav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/19/02 5:53:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5184.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.luisvazquez.net/side.jpg width=75 height=26></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span cla